is well defined.

It can be shown that the Fourier transform of formula_41 is a function (as opposed to a general tempered distribution) given at the value formula_46 by

:formula_47

and that this function can be extended to values of formula_46 in the complex space formula_40. This extension of the Fourier transform to the complex domain is called the Fourier–Laplace transform.

